{
  "stem": "2002.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "We went through, and we got on a train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we are in Austria.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In Austria, in Salzburg-- we were going to go to Germany.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In Austria, my sister gets very sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And if she got so sick that they had to take her off the train, so we went all off the train-- me, my friend, my sister, and my brother-in-law.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they took us to a camp called Reidenberg.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And-- No, I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I'm sorry.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Parsch was the camp, Parsch.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And there was barracks, brick barracks with apartments, like condominiums.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And there already must've been there about 500 families living in the condominiums, all refugees.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And Salzburg at that time was actually a transfer area from people went different places.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "People went to Israel.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "People went-- At that time, Jews couldn't go to Israel because England would let them in.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "So my sister went in in the hospital, and she got very sick.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "She got sick that that doctor told me he didn't even know if she's going to survive.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And he mentioned to me sicknesses that's not even the bug that she has.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "I find out later it's because she was in the sewer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "That's why the bug from the sewer.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "When they confiscated the ghetto in Lvov, a group of people went in to live in the sewer for 18 months.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And many times, they were in the water up to their neck, as a big storm came.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "So she was there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And the- and the doctor told me that she-- whatever she eats, she throws up.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "I should try to get her chicken soup.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 51,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "I don't know how he knew I'm Jewish because when he asked me for chicken soup, I assumed things only Jewish-- I assumed only Jews had chicken soup.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
